CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1945, pg. 15, reads: "Good Hunting - The Lawrenceville Sporting Club displays a portion of the results of a one-night hunting trip near Greece City, Butler County. Three raccoons, three 'possums, eight rabbits, and three squirrels were bagged.  Left to right: Foster Pickett, Jesse Stevens, Arthur Richardson, holding his dogs; Charlie Richardson, Joseph Jenkins and Comar Patterson, kneeling in center forefront. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Hunters, from left: Foster Pickett, Jesse Stevens, Arthur Richardson holding his dogs, Charlie Richardson, Joseph Jenkins, and Comar Patterson kneeling in center, with dead raccoons, rabbits, and opossums, in Harris Studio, another version
